First, we need to find the symmetric difference (A△B) between sets A and B. The symmetric difference is the set of elements which are in either of the sets but not in their intersection.

A = {2, 4, 6, 8, 10}
B = {3, 6, 9, 12, 15}

Intersection of A and B (A ∩ B) = {6}
A△B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B) = {2, 3, 4, 8, 9, 10, 12, 15}

Now, we need to find the symmetric difference between (A△B) and C.

(A△B) = {2, 3, 4, 8, 9, 10, 12, 15}
C = {5, 10, 15}

Intersection of (A△B) and C ((A△B) ∩ C) = {10, 15}
(A△B)△C = ((A△B) ∪ C) - ((A△B) ∩ C) = {2, 3, 4, 5, 8, 9, 12}

So, (A△B)△C = {2, 3, 4, 5, 8, 9, 12}.
